10/12/2009
BERLIN, Germany -- Macedonian Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski urged the EU on Wednesday (December 9th) not to forget the Western Balkans, including his country. He made the request at the European People's Party (EPP) congress in Bonn. Gruevski reaffirmed that talks between Macedonia and Greece on their long-standing name dispute will continue. EU foreign ministers recently decided to postpone discussions about a launch date for Macedonia's accession talks until next year, disappointing Skopje. (MIA, Alsat, Sitel - 09/12/09)
